<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
  <head>
    <title>CSS Writing Modes Test: text baseline alignment - plain text (central alignment with vertical layout)</title>
    <link rel="author" title="Hajime Shiozawa" href="mailto:hajime.shiozawa@gmail.com" />
    <link rel="help" title="4.2. Text Baseline" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-writing-modes/#text-baselines" />
    <link rel="match" href="text-baseline-003-ref.xht" />
    <meta name="assert" content="This test checks the generation of text baseline. When 'writing-mode' is vertical and 'text-orientation' is 'upright', then the central baseline is used as the dominant baseline." />
    <meta name="flags" content="ahem image" />
    <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
      div > p {
        margin: 0;
        font: 40px/1 "Ahem";
      }
      img {
        margin-top: -200px;
      }

      /* writing-mode property */
      .vertical-lr {
        writing-mode: vertical-lr;
      }

      /* text-orientation property */
      .upright {
        text-orientation: upright;
      }
  ]]></style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>Test passes if a thin blue line is centered in the black rectangle</p>
    <div class="vertical-lr">
      <p class="upright">OriUPr<img src="./support/blue-vert-line-1x220.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" /></p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
